<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.IRendererPlugin.AllocatorPointer" Title="AllocatorPointer typedef" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IRendererPlugin">IRendererPlugin</PageRef> ->
    AllocatorPointer
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Declaration">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[typedef IGraphicsDeviceEnumerator* (*AllocatorPointer)(cobalt::logging::ILogger* log);]]></Code>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>AllocatorPointer</TypeRef> typedef describes the renderer plugin function pointer used to allocate an <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IGraphicsDeviceEnumerator">IGraphicsDeviceEnumerator</PageRef>.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
      The logger pointer is transferred to the created enumerator. The enumerator is returned as a raw pointer so it can be wrapped by the shared interface smart pointer on the caller side.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
